                        <h3 class="mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-2">
                            <strong>How You Should Use Sundays</h3></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5 text-muted">The Billion Dollar Routine</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><span>S</span>undays, are weird. They’re the end of the week, you don’t have work on Sundays, but you know you have work tomorrow.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I know a ton of people who just waste their Sundays. They just sit around and do nothing. Why do anything, if tomorrow I’m going to work, better to say energy, they think. I know a ton of other people, who just party on Sundays because what better to do? And if you’re doing anything like that, you’re doing it wrong!</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">There are a couple of mistakes in that mindset & style of living!<br></br><strong>Firstly</strong>, why give up on life? Why just say, fuck it let’s do nothing?! <strong>Secondly</strong>, it’s clear to me that, that life has <strong>no structure</strong>, and even if it does it’s not the right kind of structure, or it’s set up by outside factors. <strong>Thirdly</strong>, there is a (big )lack of self-awareness.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I truly believe that Sundays are the most important days for getting the life you want. So, this is how you should be using Sundays.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Sundays </strong>should be used in <em>3 parts</em>:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Reflect </strong>— Keep track of everything you do during the week. On Sundays reflect on what you did. How you spent your time? Are you following your rules & principles? Are you doing what you we’re supposed to do, or are you doing the opposite of that? Are you advancing toward your goals?</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><mark>Reevaluate</mark><strong> </strong>— After you know what you did( I recommend having a document to structure everything in), it’s time to see what you could be doing differently, and what you will do differently. Take a time to notice your mistakes, and find a solution. It’s ok to make mistakes( obviously), but it’s <strong>NEVER</strong> ok to repeat them.<br></br>Take a look at your goals, is you’re routine helping you get there? If not, what can you change?<br></br>Reevaluate everything you’re doing. Can you do anything better? Then move on to step 3.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Plan </strong>— Now that you know what you’ve been doing. And you know what you want to be doing. Create a plan. Have a structure you can follow.<br></br>Devise a plan to do more/less of what you were/weren’t doing that you want/don’t want to do.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Sundays should set you up for the week that’s coming. They’re not to be wasted!</p></div></div></div></section><?php include_once 'Elemental/footer.php'; ?>